Parliament, Wednesday, 27 February 2019 – The Ad Hoc Committee to identify suitable candidates for the filling of vacancies at the Commission for Gender Equality has agreed to shortlist 24 candidates to be interviewed for appointment to the Commission for Gender Equality. The following are the shortlisted candidates: Ms Jennifer Smout
	Ms Esther Euphane Aletta Watson
	Ms Magdaline Moonsamy
	Mr Mbuyiselo Botha
	Dr Tlaleng Mofokeng
	Ms Mapitsi Mary Mononela
	Ms Nomasonto Grace Mazibuko
	Non-binary Busisiwe Deyi
	Ms Nomsisi Lindelwa Batha
	Ms Tasneem Fredericks
	Mr Louis Laurens Botha Gaum
	Ms Kedisaletse Rachel Matlhaba
	Ms Mmabatho Eugenia Ramagoshi
	Ms Lindiwe Octavia Ntuli-Tloubatla
	Prof Renier Steyn
	Ms Liliwe Eliza Mlilwana
	Ms Ayanda Mfusi
	Ms Mummy Nomvulazana Constance Jafta
	Ms Priscilla Lynnette Fundisile Nzimande
	Ms Ohara Diseko
	Ms Mothupi Getrude Dibeela
	Prof Thidziambi Sylvia Phendla
	Ms Elizabeth Margaretha Lemmer
	Mr Bhekizenzo Tembe The committee has agreed to schedule interviews over two days, on 12 and 13 March 2019. ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE AD HOC COMMITTEE TO IDENTIFY SUITABLE CANDIDATES FOR THE FILLING OF VACANCIES AT THE COMMISSION FOR GENDER EQUALITY, MS NONHLANHLA NCUBE-NDABA. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson please contact: Name: Ms Yoliswa Landu
